FBIS3-13942 "drnes055_j_94002" FBIS-NES-94-055 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Mar 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA United Arab Emirates Paper Reports Media `Distortion' of Clinton Remarks JN2103211394 Abu Dhabi AL-ITTIHAD in Arabic 18 Mar 94 p 26 JN2103211394 Abu Dhabi AL-ITTIHAD Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Huda Tawfiq Reprt from Washington] [Text] U.S. President Bill Clinton has voiced his discomfort over the media's distortion of his stand on Jerusalem, which some sides interpreted as an approval of Israel's position that unified Jerusalem is Israel's capital. A U.S. State Department official told AL-ITTIHAD that the United States regrets such a distortion of President Clinton's position and stresses that the U.S. position on Jerusalem has not changed and that Clinton had announced that the status of Jerusalem would be decided during negotiations in accordance with the contents of the Palestinian-Israeli Declaration of Principles.
